00:33:19,268 --> 00:33:22,449
Evan asks, What are some of your favorite methods

678
00:33:22,549 --> 00:33:25,270
for avoiding unplayable cut scenes? Mm.

679
00:33:27,759 --> 00:33:32,160
You mean like in terms of like when I'm working on a project, how do we keep from like defaulting to a...

680
00:33:34,301 --> 00:33:40,943
Yes. I won't specify, but let's go with that. Yeah. If they want to amend their question, I'll get to that.

681
00:33:40,963 --> 00:33:44,804
Okay. Yeah, I'm being ridiculous. I'm like, what, you mean like when I play, do I skip cutscenes?

682
00:33:44,824 --> 00:33:50,986
But I'm sure he means what I just said. Okay. Yeah, so...

683
00:33:53,317 --> 00:33:57,079
Well, I'm not opposed to cut scenes as a blanket statement,

684
00:33:57,760 --> 00:34:01,502
but I am opposed to story and gameplay being really separate.

685
00:34:01,662 --> 00:34:06,284
So for example, if there's a real push on a project

