00:34:06,324 --> 00:34:10,847
for using cut scenes, what I want to do is use cut scenes.

687
00:34:11,027 --> 00:34:11,487
Here, you know what?

688
00:34:11,507 --> 00:34:12,948
I'm going to be specific and use an example.

689
00:34:13,128 --> 00:34:14,789
I'll tell you a game that I think did a great job

690
00:34:14,809 --> 00:34:17,110
with cut scenes is the original God of War.

691
00:34:18,417 --> 00:34:21,437
because when you play the God of War, Athena comes to you and says,

692
00:34:22,198 --> 00:34:25,699
Ares has gone mad and only you, the strongest Spartan, can kill the God of War.

693
00:34:25,779 --> 00:34:30,060
Will you do it? And if you go back and you watch a cinematic on YouTube,

694
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:34,641
he doesn't say, hell yeah, I'll kill the God of War. I hate that guy.

695
00:34:34,681 --> 00:34:37,122
He sucks. Like it's not a revenge story.

696
00:34:37,782 --> 00:34:42,303
What he actually says is I'll do it if you take these memories away from me.

697
00:34:44,157 --> 00:34:45,439
And this is the beginning of the game.

698
00:34:45,459 --> 00:34:46,340
I'm like, what memories?

699
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,081
Did I miss something?

700
00:34:47,181 --> 00:34:47,562
What memories?

701
00:34:47,582 --> 00:34:48,083
What's going on?

702
00:34:48,704 --> 00:34:51,928
And so as the game progresses, we get to see more and more of his

703
00:34:51,988 --> 00:34:56,574
memories, which are revealed in bits and pieces, which are huge payoffs for me.

704
00:34:56,634 --> 00:34:57,816
I've been waiting for that.

705
00:34:58,782 --> 00:35:01,704
right, because this mystery was set up ahead of time

706
00:35:02,204 --> 00:35:03,725
and the cut scenes play out in such a way

707
00:35:03,745 --> 00:35:04,906
that they give me just enough,

708
00:35:04,946 --> 00:35:07,388
they close a loop and they open a loop at the same time.

709
00:35:08,529 --> 00:35:09,750
They really keep me on the hook.

710
00:35:09,830 --> 00:35:12,612
And so for me, and it turns out that what's happening

711
00:35:12,632 --> 00:35:13,873
in the memories he's trying to forget

712
00:35:14,073 --> 00:35:16,395
is tied to the gameplay in ways that become

713
00:35:17,135 --> 00:35:19,177
not clear at first, but become clearer and clearer

714
00:35:19,217 --> 00:35:20,137
as the game goes on.

715
00:35:20,258 --> 00:35:22,699
So that to me is like a magic trick.

716
00:35:22,939 --> 00:35:25,021
Like it is cut scene based storytelling

717
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:26,762
but deeply integrated with gameplay.

718
00:35:28,905 --> 00:35:32,931
And that's, you know, cutscenes are just a tool, a weak tool, right?

719
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,653
Dialogue is your weakest tool.

720
00:35:35,174 --> 00:35:36,616
Second weakest tool is cutscenes.

721
00:35:37,257 --> 00:35:40,542
But they can be used well if they're just used carefully.

